  "text": "Two kinds of triangulation were conducted: data triangulation (use of multiple groups of research participants) and investigator triangulation (use of multiple researchers in data analysis) [CITATION_1] . Triangulation methods focussed on comparing and contrasting both HCP groups' perceptions of barriers and facilitators within each of the theoretical domains with a view to guiding the research team's decisions as to how selected BCTs could eventually be operationalised as part of an intervention.",
